text: Kieran Ault-Connell (born 30 July 1981) is an Australian athlete with cerebral palsy. He was born in Melbourne. At the 2000 Summer Paralympics, he won two gold medals in the men's relay T38 and men's relay T38 races. At the 2004 Summer Paralympics, he won a silver medal in the Men's Javelin F37 event. == References == Category:Australian athletes Category:Paralympic gold medalists for Australia Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Australia Category:1981 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Melbourne Category:2000 Summer Paralympics Category:2004 Summer Paralympics
